race.comment: ROYAL GLADIATOR (8) went forward and proved too strong last time out, scoring by 1.5L over 1300m at Sunshine Coast. Will be up on the pace again and won at his only go over this distance. Finds a suitable assignment and can get the job done. GOOGAZ (4) was an impressive winner over 1400m at Gatton, stalking the pace before lengthening nicely to score by 3.5L. Will push forward and only has to hold that form to threaten. DENETTA (5) was quickly back on track placing at Ipswich in stronger over 1666m. She looks ready to win but has the outside barrier and will need luck. MISHANI REACTOR (2) scored two runs back and then wasn't ridden out over a mile at Gympie when the jockey was concerned he may have had an issue. He's been kept on the fresh side, and Huxtable goes aboard today. He can bounce back into the money if presented on song.
